1. What is Flow Builder?

Flow Builder is a Salesforce automation tool that allows users to create automated business processes using a graphical interface without writing code. It helps organizations automate repetitive tasks, improve efficiency, reduce errors, and streamline workflows.

Key Features:
Drag-and-drop interface
No coding required
Automates business processes
Creates guided user experiences
Integrates with Salesforce records and data
Benefits:
Saves time
Reduces manual work
Improves data accuracy
Enhances user productivity
2. Types of Flows

Salesforce provides several types of flows, including:

Screen Flow
Record-Triggered Flow
Scheduled Flow
Autolaunched Flow
Platform Event-Triggered Flow
A. Screen Flow

A Screen Flow is an interactive flow that displays screens to users and collects input.

Characteristics:
User interaction required
Displays forms and screens
Can update records based on user input
Example:

A customer support agent fills out a complaint form. The Screen Flow collects customer details and automatically creates a case record.

Use Cases:
Employee onboarding forms
Customer feedback collection
Service request forms
Survey applications
B. Record-Triggered Flow

A Record-Triggered Flow automatically runs when a Salesforce record is created, updated, or deleted.

Characteristics:
Fully automated
Runs in the background
No user interaction required
Example:

When a new customer account is created, the flow automatically sends a welcome email and creates follow-up tasks.

Use Cases:
Automatic email notifications
Record updates
Approval process initiation
Task creation
